    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-11-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="476"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/516.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister for Foreign Affairs</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Wilson</hi>: The President of the Republic has
                    referred to me the matter mentioned in your excellency’s letter of the 18th
                    instant, namely, the exaggerated anti-American articles published by a paper in
                    this city. I have taken steps to suppress such articles, as unjust and
                    unpatriotic, and your excellency has doubtless observed that such articles have
                    ceased to appear in the paper referred to.</p>
                <p>I highly appreciate the interest your excellency is taking in keeping the
                    relations between Mexico and the United States as cordial and friendly as ever,
                    and I assure you that such is the feeling of the President, and the spirit of
                    the international policy confided to me.</p>
                <p>I avail [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Enrique C. Creel.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
